            ],
            "secId": "sec2.4",
            "sentence": "We will study both for the GSSCM.",
            "startOffset": 97547,
            "title": "Robustness properties"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 89711,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "Like classical PCA, spherical PCA aims to find a lower dimensional subspace that captures most of the variability in the data.",
            "startOffset": 89585,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 88987,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b20": {
                    "endOffset": 88919,
                    "startOffset": 88915
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "Somewhat surprisingly, this transformation yields a consistent estimator of the eigenvectors of the true covariance matrix [20] under relatively general conditions on the underlying distribution.",
            "startOffset": 88792,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 89584,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b17": {
                    "endOffset": 89583,
                    "startOffset": 89571
                },
                "b30": {
                    "endOffset": 89583,
                    "startOffset": 89571
                },
                "b32": {
                    "endOffset": 89583,
                    "startOffset": 89571
                },
                "b5": {
                    "endOffset": 89583,
                    "startOffset": 89571
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "The most common use of the SSCM is probably in the context of (functional) spherical PCA as developed in [5,17,30,32].",
            "startOffset": 89466,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 109758,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec5",
            "sentence": "The spatial sign covariance matrix (SSCM) can be seen as a member of a larger class called Generalized SSCM (GSSCM) estimators in which other radial functions are allowed.",
            "startOffset": 109587,
            "title": "Conclusions"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 87903,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "Over the last decades, many robust estimators for the covariance matrix have been developed.",
            "startOffset": 87811,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 110104,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec5",
            "sentence": "We have studied five GSSCM methods with intuitively appealing radial functions, and shown that their asymptotic breakdown values are as high as that of the original SSCM.",
            "startOffset": 109934,
            "title": "Conclusions"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 88426,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "This means that the estimators commute with orthogonal transformations, which are characterized by orthogonal matrices and include rotations and reflections.",
            "startOffset": 88269,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 89152,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b31": {
                    "endOffset": 89104,
                    "startOffset": 89100
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "Of course the eigenvalues are different from the eigenvalues of the true covariance matrix, but it was shown in [31] that the order of the eigenvalues is preserved.",
            "startOffset": 88988,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 96634,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec2",
                    "title": "Methodology"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec2.3",
            "sentence": "C-step",
            "startOffset": 96628,
            "title": "Location estimator"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 97466,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec2",
                    "title": "Methodology"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec2.4",
            "sentence": "A major reason for the SSCM\u2019s popularity is its robustness against outliers.",
            "startOffset": 97390,
            "title": "Robustness properties"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 90634,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b10": {
                    "endOffset": 90633,
                    "startOffset": 90625
                },
                "b7": {
                    "endOffset": 90633,
                    "startOffset": 90625
                },
                "b9": {
                    "endOffset": 90633,
                    "startOffset": 90625
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In addition to spherical PCA, there also has been a lot of recent research on the use of the SSCM for constructing robust correlation estimators [7,9,10].",
            "startOffset": 90480,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 90109,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "The directions (\u2018loadings\u2019) of spherical PCA thus correspond to the eigenvectors of the SSCM scatter matrix.",
            "startOffset": 90001,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 91465,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b28": {
                    "endOffset": 91328,
                    "startOffset": 91324
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "Serneels et al. [28] use the spatial sign transform as an initial preprocessing step in order to obtain a robust version of partial least squares regression.",
            "startOffset": 91308,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 111191,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec5",
            "sentence": "A potential topic for further research is to investigate principal component analysis based on a GSSCM covariance matrix.",
            "startOffset": 111070,
            "title": "Conclusions"
        }
